<span id="iv.x.cvi-p1"></span> *CVI. To Abraham the Œconomus.*

<span id="iv.x.cvi-p2"></span>By the godly bishops I salute you. I
beseech you to give heed to the churches’ calm, and to disperse the
waves of calumny. “Whatsoever a man soweth that shall he also
reap,” <span id="fr_1841"></span>[1842](#fn_1841.md) as says the divine
Apostle. Without doubt then he who fights for the apostolic doctrines
shall reap the fruit of the apostolic blessing and enjoy the Apostles’
devotion.

